of a small X-ray flare just after a very fast rise in\nhard X-ray flux. In contrast, the source remained undetected by MAGIC at the\npeak of a larger X-ray flare occurring one day later and corresponding to the\nmaximum of the X-ray luminosity of the whole outburst. We do not find any\nobvious correlation between the X-ray and TeV emission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 May 2008 17:10:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 18 Sep 2008 10:44:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
