onsidering our present ignorance of the role of collisions\nwith hydrogen atoms on the NLTE level populations of oxygen, is\nlog(Noxygen/Nhydrogen) = 8.76 +- 0.07. The reasons which have led to lower O\nabundances in the past are identified as (1) the lower equivalent widths\nadopted, and (2) the choice of neglecting collisions with hydrogen atoms in the\nstatistical equilibrium calculations for oxygen.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 May 2008 18:22:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-18"}
